<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF206-949-736  </DOCNO><DOCID>06 949 736.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Magazine  Feb 14 1989 v8 n3 p436(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Science Toolkit lets you explore the world of physics.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Cohen, Alan.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Broderbund Software Inc. (products).andO;Product:   Science Toolkit (Computer program) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     PhysicsSoftware packagesEvaluation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Science Toolkit Lets You Explore the World Of Physics Kitchen tables acrossAmerica are going to be a whole lot cleaner from now on.andP;  That's becauseScience Toolkit, from Broderbund Software, turns any PC into a sophisticated,messfree home laboratory.andM;The Science Toolkit Master Module provides the budding rocket scientist withall the tools he needs to begin exploring the laws of physics.andP;  Two specialprobes are included: a thermistor to measure temperature and a photocell tomeasure light intensity.andP;  When plugged into the program's interface box(which connects to a game port), these probes control the four on-screeninstruments: a thermometer, a light meter, a timer, and a strip chart.andM;The user guide carefully explains all the experiments, and it includesinteresting sidebars that recount important scientific discoveries and facts.andM;The experiments themselves are not very exciting.andP;  There's a limit to theamount of fun one can have watching the temperature of hot water in aStyrofoam cup gradually drop.andP;  Luckily, Module 1: Speed and Motion (soldseparately) livens things up.andP;  Two on-screen instruments--a speedometer and atachometer--an additional photocell probe, and a balloon-powered car areincluded.andM;As part of an experiment on acceleration, the two photocells, which will beused to control the speedometer, are inserted through slots 6 inches apart ina special cardboard stand.andP;  When the front wheels of the Lego-style car passbefore the first photocell, they break the beam of light striking the probeand activate the speedometer's timer.andP;  When the wheels pass the secondphotocell, the timer stops and the speedometer calculates the speed of thecar.andM;At $79.95 for the Master Module and $39.95 for Module 1, the program may be abit pricey, but, hey, balloon-powered cars don't come cheap.andO;</TEXT></DOC>